        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2020-07-02 11:45:50.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> Patch Set 2:\n> \n> > Patch Set 2:\n> > \n> > not sure to see the dependency with the patch \"optimize size\" here\n> > the other patch cannot be merged as it is breaking several linters\n> > but it looks like you submitted thsi patch on top of the other one creating a dependency chain\n> > I cannot submit this patch alone\n> \n> The is a particular line in Dockerfile that is changed by both CR.\n> In the \"Patch Set 1\" I've tried to submit this CR alone but then I was warned about the conflict with the \"optimize size\" CR.\n> Is there a way to force the submission of this CR as a standalone patch?\n\nGerrit info about merge conflict for two not already submitted CRs is just informational and not a blocker. The commiter whose review get merged as last will have to rebase and resolve the merge conflict, that's all. \n\nRebase your commit onto master, or cherry pick it to master in your local clone. Some hints on using \"onto\" option you can find on my miniblog post:  https://500ok.tumblr.com/post/612927802463879168/version-control\n\nIf you're still unsure let me know in a comment, I can rebase it for you.",
